Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potato{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need
to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out and roast on the top shelf
until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Put the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} on
another #tray{} on the middle shelf and roast until golden brown,
~{20-25%minutes}. Turn both halfway.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. When hot,
add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{60%g}. Stir-fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook
lardons thoroughly. Add the @onion marmalade{40%g} and @water{1%tbsp} (for the
jam) into the pan, bubble for ~{30%seconds}, then transfer to a #bowl{}. Set
aside.

Return the #saucepan{} to high heat with a drizzle of oil. When hot, add the
@British Beef Mince{120%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT:
Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Break it up as it cooks.
Discard any excess fat, then season. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @green chilli{1},
then add half to the browned mince with the @Worcester Sauce{1/2%tbsp}.
Evaporate the sauce, then stir in the @Tomato Passata{1/2%cup}, @water{50%ml} and
a @sugar{pinch}. Bring to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer until
thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, combine the @Mayonnaise{1%tbsp} and @Red Wine Vinegar{1%tbsp} in a
bowl along with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}
and toss to coat. Split open the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2} and grate the
@Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}.

When the sausages and beef chilli are ready, remove the tray with the sausages
from the #oven{} and preheat the #grill{} to high (move the potatoes down to the
bottom shelf). IMPORTANT: The sausages and mince are cooked when no longer pink
in the middle. Put the buns on the baking tray and pop a sausage in each.
Carefully spoon the chilli inside the bun, then sprinkle over the cheese.
Grill until golden and bubbly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Finish the filled brioche buns with a spoonful of bacon jam and a few slices of
the remaining chilli. Serve with the fries and slaw divided between your plates.

> Don't be afraid to get messy!